  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sri Lanka Flood Initial Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is an initial response to the flooding disaster in Sri Lanka starting 25 May 2017. More than 650,000 people were affected across 15 districts. Urgent needs included food, water and sanitation, health, and shelter. Our response will focus on dry food kits as well as an NFI and Hygiene kit.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We distributed to 1,589 households in total with 767 families receiving a dry rations food kit and 767 families receiving NFI kits. Additionally, 55 families received both kits.</narrative>
  </description>
